710599f-a.title: Manhattan: 11th Avenue - 21st Street (West)
710599f-a.text:
Eleventh Avenue, east side, at W. 21at Street (center) as
viewed north eastward to show at the right a billboard announcing
the planned Memorial Building of the Seamens Christian Association
which Aas founded in 1888 and is now located at No. 399 West Street.
Personal observation in the Fall of 1938 fails to show any improve-
ment of this site. The Seamen's House of the Y.M.C.A. is now in
this wicinity, beinm No. 55O Nest 20th Street, a t the S.E. corner
of the Avenue and would be to the richt if shown.
April 3, 1929,
